******
[2] Nebraska
Date: Wed 12 Feb 2020
Source: RFDTV [edited]
https://www.rfdtv.com/story/41692573/nebraska-horse-confirmed-with-ehv


An 8-year-old Quarter Horse in Nebraska was confirmed to have equine herpesvirus on 6 Feb 2020.

According to the TheHorse.Com (https://thehorse.com/184847/nebraska-horse-confirmed-with-equine-herpesvirus-1/), the mare began showing signs of fever on 4 Feb 2020. She had been vaccinated and is recovering; however, a voluntary quarantine on 30 horses was put in place.

EHV-1 is highly contagious in horses, and many times signs can initially go undetected. Signs include cough, decreased appetite, depression and nasal discharge.

