[Biosecurity is extremely important with this disease, as it is highly contagious and spreads easily. There is no vaccine against the neurological form of the disease. Current EHV-1 vaccines might reduce viral shedding but are not protective against the neurologic form of the disease. Implementing routine biosecurity practices is the best way to minimize viral spread, and the best method of disease control is disease prevention. - Mod.TG

